"   <div id=\"basicsTopicLeft\">",
"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Epilepsy and pregnancy (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/epilepsy-and-pregnancy-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157353\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is epilepsy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Epilepsy is a condition that causes people to have repeated seizures. Seizures are waves of abnormal electrical activity in the brain. Seizures can make you pass out, or move or behave strangely.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157368\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can women with epilepsy have a normal pregnancy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Most women with epilepsy can have a healthy pregnancy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If you have epilepsy and want to have a baby, you will need to work closely with your doctors. They will make sure that you are doing the right things to control your epilepsy and protect your baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      More than 1 doctor will take care of you during pregnancy. One doctor will take care of your pregnancy. Your epilepsy doctor will take care of your epilepsy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157383\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What should I do before trying to get pregnant?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;It is very important to talk with your doctor",
"      <strong>",
"       before",
"      </strong>",
"      you try to get pregnant. That way, he or she has enough time to check your anti-seizure medicine and change it, if needed. That&rsquo;s because certain anti-seizure medicines and doses can harm an unborn baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Your doctor might:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Change your anti-seizure medicine &ndash; He or she will make sure that your anti-seizure medicine is safe to take during pregnancy.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Stop your anti-seizure medicine &ndash; If you have not had any seizures for 2 years, your doctor might talk with you about stopping your medicine. But don&rsquo;t ever stop an anti-seizure medicine on your own.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Lower your dose of anti-seizure medicine",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Reduce the number of anti-seizure medicines you take (if you take more than 1)",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      In addition to checking your medicine, your doctor might prescribe a vitamin called &ldquo;folate&rdquo; or &ldquo;",
"      <a class=\"drug drug_patient\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?24/57/25492?source=see_link\">",
"       folic acid",
"      </a>",
"      .&rdquo; All women who are trying to get pregnant should take folate, because it helps prevent birth defects. Women who take certain anti-seizure medicines might need extra folate.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      There are also steps that all women should take before trying to get pregnant. (See",
"      <a class=\"medical medical_basics\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?37/1/37907?source=see_link\">",
"       \"Patient information: How to plan and prepare for a healthy pregnancy (The Basics)\"",
"      </a>",
"      .)",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157400\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How might my epilepsy affect my baby?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Having seizures while you are pregnant might harm your baby. If you fall down, you could hurt yourself and your baby. When you have a seizure, your baby might not get enough oxygen.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157415\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Does pregnancy affect epilepsy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Not usually. Being pregnant will probably not make you have more seizures. But you could have more seizures if you don&rsquo;t follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and take your anti-seizure medicine (if you need medicine). &nbsp;",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157430\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How can I lower my chances of having a seizure?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;To lower your chances of having a seizure, you can:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Take your anti-seizure medicine exactly as directed &ndash; Do not stop or change your medicine without talking to your doctor. You might worry that your anti-seizure medicine will harm your baby. There is some chance that the medicine could do harm, but having a seizure can also harm your baby.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Let your doctor know if you start any new prescription or non-prescription medicines, or herbal drugs",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Get enough sleep &ndash; Not getting enough sleep raises your chances of having a seizure.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Eat a healthy diet",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157445\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Will I have tests during pregnancy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. You will have tests to check your baby&rsquo;s health. These can include blood tests and an imaging test called an ultrasound. An ultrasound creates pictures of your baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      You might also have blood tests to check the amount of anti-seizure medicine in your body.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157460\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can I have a normal vaginal delivery?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Most women can have a normal vaginal delivery. It is uncommon for women to have a seizure during delivery. Even so, your doctor will watch you closely during your delivery and adjust your medicine, if needed.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157475\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Will my baby be healthy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;If your epilepsy was under control during your pregnancy, chances are very good that your baby will be healthy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157490\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Will I be able to breastfeed?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Most women are able to breastfeed. If you want to breastfeed, talk with your doctor. He or she will make sure that your anti-seizure medicine is safe to take if you breastfeed.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157505\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What else can I do to protect my baby?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;If you have frequent seizures, there are things you can do to help keep your baby safe after he or she is born. You can:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Change your baby&rsquo;s diaper on the floor &ndash; That way, if you have a seizure, your baby won&rsquo;t fall off a changing table.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have someone else with you when you bathe your baby &ndash; That way, your baby won&rsquo;t be alone in the bathtub if you have a seizure.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H10157527\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
